The paper discusses empirical comparison of planners in the field of planning research, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the methodology used for these comparisons, which involves running planners on a subset of problems, and examines assumptions about the problems, planners, and metrics used in these comparisons. This methodology and analysis could also fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), robotics (cs.RO), software engineering (cs.SE), and programming languages (cs.PL).
